<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07831</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INSTITUTIONALIZING THE TREATMENT OF ACTIVE MILITARY PERSONNEL WITH POST-TRAUMATIC STRESS DISORDER AND PROVIDING FUNDS THEREFOR AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Recognizes the relevance of the advent of increasing awareness on the issue of mental health as it relates to the country’s Armed Forces; Aims to institutionalize the treatment and prevention of post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) for the benefit of the country’s Armed Forces.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-05-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-08-01)</td><td>2. Bataoil (000 2018-08-06)</td><tr><td>3. Tambunting (000 2018-10-07)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON NATIONAL DEFENSE AND SECURITY ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>